               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380917-name-852" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-852" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-852" type="surname" value="LAWRENCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-852" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE LAWRENCE</persName>
                  </hi>. My father's name is James—he keeps a shop in the New-cut, Lambeth—I lost a prayer-book from there on the 19th of July-James Newman came, and produced it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380917-name-853" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-853" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-853" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-853" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES NEWMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 36.) On Thursday, the 19th of July, I followed the prisoner in the Westminster-bridge-road—he went down the New-cut, made a stop at Mr. Lawrence's shop, looked at several things, and took up the prayer-book with his right hand—he put it under his coat, and went off—I went and took it from him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I was walking down the New-cut, took up this book, and looked at it—the policeman came and took me, and said I wanted to steal it—I had not got away from the shop. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. He had got a dozen yards from the shop, and would have gone further if I had not stopped him.</p>
